":"Ireland, Orkney, Scotland, United Kingdom","Parsonstown, County Offaly, Ireland, United Kingdom":"Parsonstown, County Offaly, Ireland","Cavan, County Tyrone, Ireland":"Cavan, County Tyrone, Ireland","Ely, Kilkenny, Leinster, Ireland":"Leinster, Ireland","nameMeanings":[{"name":"O'Brien","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Irish Brendan, Dermot, Liam, Brigid, Declan, Donovan, John Patrick, Kieran, Colm, Donal, Brennan, Caitlin.","Irish: Anglicized form of Gaelic <b>Ó Briain</b> ‘descendant of <i>Brian</i>’, a personal name probably based on the element <i>bre-</i> ‘hill’, with the transferred sense ‘eminence’, i.e. ‘exalted one’. See also   Bryan  . In Ireland there has also been some confusion with   O'Byrne   (see   Byrne  ).","History: This name is borne in particular by one of the greatest of Irish septs, descendants of Brian Boru, who rose to the high kingship of Ireland in 1002."],"variants":[{"name":"O'Brion","meanings":["Irish: variant of   O'Brien  ."]},{"name":"O'Bryon","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Irish William Kevin.","Irish: variant of   O'Brien  ."]},{"name":"Bryan","meanings":["English and Irish: variant of   Bryant  .","Irish: shortened Anglicized form of <b>Ó Briain</b>, see   O'Brien  ."]},{"name":"O'Briant","meanings":["Irish: variant of   O'Brien  , with excrescent <i>-t</i>."]},{"name":"O'Bryant","meanings":["Irish: variant of   O'Brien  ."]},{"name":"McBrien","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Irish Brendan, Seamus.","Irish:","Anglicized form of Gaelic <b>Mac Briain</b> ‘son of Brian’. See   O'Brien   and   Bryan  ."]},{"name":"O'Brian","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Irish Liam.","Irish: variant of   O'Brien  ."]},{"name":"O'Bryan","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Irish James Patrick, Padraic.","Irish: variant of   O'Brien  ."]}]},{"name":"Bibiana","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Spanish: variant of <b>Bibián</b> (see   Bibian  ). This surname is most common in Mexico.","Italian: habitational name from a place called Bibiana, in Torino province."],"variants":[{"name":"Bibian","meanings":["Spanish and Galician (<b>Bibián</b>): from the personal name <i>Bibián</i>, a variant of <i>Vivián</i> (see   Vivian  )."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"When Lady Bibiana O'Brien was born about 1370, in Parsonstown, County Offaly, Ireland, her father, Turlogh O'Brien Bishop Killloe, was 19 and her mother, Lady Maria O'Brien, was 9. She had at least 1 daughter with Gildas O'Reilly, Lord of East Breffny. She died in 1395, in Ireland, Orkney, Scotland, United Kingdom, at the age of 26."},"et":{"Abt 1370–1395":"umbes 1370–1395","1370–1395":"1370–1395","1401–Male":"1401–Surnud","1360–Male":"1360–Surnud","1395–1445":"1395–1445","1353–1428":"1353–1428","1362–1420":"1362–1420","Abt 1370":"umbes 1370","1445":"1445","1401":"1401","1420":"1420","1353":"1353","1395":"1395","1362":"1362","1382":"1382","1360":"1360","1370":"1370","1428":"1428","Leinster, Ireland, United Kingdom":"Ireland, Orkney, Šotimaa, United Kingdom","Parsonstown, County Offaly, Ireland, United Kingdom":"Parsonstown, County Offaly, Iirimaa","Cavan, County Tyrone, Ireland":"Cavan, County Tyrone, Iirimaa","Ely, Kilkenny, Leinster, Ireland":"Leinster, Iirimaa"},"fi":{"Abt 1370–1395":"noin 1370–1395","1370–1395":"1370–1395","1401–Male":"1401–Kuollut","1360–Male":"1360–Kuollut","1395–1445":"1395–1445","1353–1428":"1353–1428","1362–1420":"1362–1420","Abt 1370":"noin 1370","1445":"1445","1401":"1401","1420":"1420","1353":"1353","1395":"1395","1362":"1362","1382":"1382","1360":"1360","1370":"1370","1428":"1428","Leinster, Ireland, United Kingdom":"Ireland, Orkney, Skotlanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Parsonstown, County Offaly, Ireland, United Kingdom":"Parsonstown, County Offaly, Irlanti","Cavan, County Tyrone, Ireland":"Cavan, County Tyrone, Irlanti","